\section{INTRODUCTION}

The definition of a gravitational energy momentum tensor (GEMT)is a long standing problem in  general relativity$[1]$.To derive the the expression of the GEMT is a significant and fundamental problem in general relativity and its derivation is very useful for other fields of general relativity. There have been proposed several definitions  of GEMT. However,  they are different from each other and are not proper tensors $[2]$.\par

   In this paper we make a proper GEMT by using  Noether theorem$[3]$. What is important is that the general coordinate transformation must be written with  tetrads in the Noether theorem. It induces the GEMT, which has a index of the local Lorentz frame and it ensures the energy conservation law. \par
The organization of this paper is a following. In section II,we derive the GEMT through Noether theorem. In the Noether theorem, energy momentum tensor depends on the volume terms and surface terms in the action. In general relativity there are some physically different ways of the decomposition into the volume terms and surface ones. But they are  two different ways in mathematically. Although the definition of the energy momentum tensor of Noether theorem induces  different formulas in the different decomposition,we can show that they are same with identities.\par 
The GEMT which is obtained by above method is not symmetric. But we acquire a symmetric GEMT with a conservation law of a spin angular momentum tensor. When we consider a restricted region of space time, we have to introduce Gibbons-Hawking term(GH term)$[4]$ in the action. According to GH term, we have to add  extra terms in GEMT. \par
  In section III, we evaluate the gravitational energies of a gravitational wave$[5]$, Schwarzschild black hole and  Friedman-Lemertre-Robertoson-Walker(FLRW) universe$[6]$. As for the gravitational wave, an energy flow of gravitational wave is well known. But its quantity is different in some literature $[2]$. We can derive the energy flow  and an energy density of gravitational wave. We can calculate the gravitational energy  of the Schwarzschild black hole in and out region of the horizon. All of the gravitational energy exists only out of the horizon. The effect of GH term plays the important role in this calculation.  In the FLRW universe, the sum of  gravitational energy and the matter one becomes zero everywhere.\par
Section IV is devoted to conclusions and discussion.\par


