\section{CONCLUSIONS}
In this paper, with the Noether theorem, we make the symmetric and proper gravitational energy momentum tensor of general relativity. The conservation law of the  energy momentum tensor is satisfied. The gravitational energy momentum tensor has the world coordinate index and the local Lorenz one. It is a reason why the energy conservation law transforms covariantly under the general coordinate transformation. The  theories which have other local symmetry of space time  than the general coordinate invariance, such as Poincare gravity$[4]$, could not have a gravitational energy momentum tensor. Because the other local symmetry breaks the energy conservation law. Researchers of teleparallel gravity are proposing GEMT different from ours.[7] Their GEMT is not symmetric and
the effect of GH term is not included. Even if we start from the formula of teleparallel equivalent general relativity Eq.$( \ref{TEGR})$, our procedure  leads the same GEMT Eqs.$(\ref{GEMT4}),(\ref{GH1})$ and $(\ref{GH2})$.\par
   We derive the gravitational energies of the gravitational wave, Schwarzschid black hole and FLRW universe. The energy density and the energy flow of the gravitational wave are $(kA)^2/32\pi$. The gravitational energy of  Schwarzschid black hole exists only outer region of horizon. This is a very remarkable fact. In the FLRW universe, gravitational energy and the matter energy cancel each other out everywhere. \par


